SIMPLE: offal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: offal
<hw>of"fal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Off</ets> +
<ets>fall</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The rejected or waste parts of
any process, especially the inedible parts of a butchered animal, such
as the viscera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dead body; carrion.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is thrown away as worthless or unfit for
use; refuse; rubbish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>offals</qex> of other professions.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>off-and-on</ent>⟦br⟧
